<br>
Now I am not doing this just to stir up shit, and I'm not doing it to be an ass to smaller guilds. However I am curious as to what peoples opinions are, it is almost to the point now where some rotations are a burden for some, but there are others to look foreward too. I suppose the best way to look at it would be, when CiW made the argument for FFA like they always did there was the point of there being plenty of mobs to do with Velious, semi true then (although not really) it seems to be true now. There is a whole lot of stuff to do, just depends on what poison you prefer is. Without rotations it would come down to more of a issue of who wants what on patch days, not who gets what. Because NB still kills statue as a rotation, but unless NB wants to do AoW then I am a guild who just now got on the Statue rotation would be camping his spawn point every minute waiting for him in full force, thus freeing up other areas of the server.<br>
<br>
Flip side of that is the fact that, velious mobs and luclin mobs just aren't as hard anymore. Wouldn't surprise me if down the line Statue was able to be killed by a group of 6, I mean its not that outlandish to think but you never know. So that would come down to whether or not the top guilds on the server wanted to just send their guild out in teams to kill as much as they could on patch day. That brings us back to respect, and really thats what the Rathe is built on moreso then a Calendar or a Rotation system. I look at these as more of a ritual then a necessity. I do not doubt if they did not exist that the rathe would still function rather well just due to gentlemens agreements and the like, or just plain server rules. <br>
<br>
So anyways that's how I'm looking at it, don't know why I thought of it but I figured it'd be something to talk about. Put it in the flame forum because it will turn into a flame, because it just will. <br>
<br>
Once again, not shouting for FFA, or saying rotations suck. Just a little something to talk about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xeddrc>Xedd RC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>LOM</span><br>  Posts: 567<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(11/20/02 11:48:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=853.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotations, still necessary?</span><hr size=1> Forgot to add, my opinion is my own and not that of LoM, i'm sure several of my members disagree with my opinion as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kitofvols>Kit of VoLS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(11/21/02 1:24:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=853.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.coolarchive.com/gifanimations/animals/kitty.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotations, still necessary?</span><hr size=1> I have played on servers with no rotation, there are no gentlemen with no rotation, and sometimes there still aren't gentlemen WITH rotation.<br>
<br>
What you state above would work well for the big guilds, but would ultimately be bad for smaller guilds or guilds trying to get on rotation.<br>
<br>
With rotation there is always a chance the guild that is up for a specific mob may let a guild that is not on rotation have a try, I know we have been blessed with that chance and have repaid it.<br>
<br>
I came from a no rotation server and it sucked bad, really bad, for everyone but the biggest guild on the server.  Course back then there were a lot less mobs to kill.  No Kunark +.<br>
<br>
I would like to see Sev off rotation though, that wait for green scales sucks.  Some guilds are struggling for a green scale while others have a bunch banked.  Just the way the cookie crumbles I guess.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abazagaroth>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(11/21/02 1:40:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=853.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.modernhumanorigins.com/images/webring.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotations, still necessary?</span><hr size=1> Rotations = good<br>
<br>
The whole argument of &quot;why is X still on rotation?&quot; doesn't fly, because the simple fact is every guild on that rotation still has enough incentive to go out and kill the mob on their turn. If they had no incentive, they would remove themselves, if they couldn't kill it, they wouldn't be on the list in the first place.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but a rotation is needed the MOST for something like sev. Because the guilds wanting to dump the rotation are those that sev is very desired because of lack of hate giving warrior weapons in their guilds while they are moving into higher end stuff. They want the rotation dropped because it will benefit them the most. They have the capacity to get together a raid to kill sev on short notice, a larger guild still on the rotation (like TL) won't have the incentive to really &quot;race&quot; (as in stop what they are doing, have people camping the zone watching for him to pop, the kind of stuff that happens with highly desired race mobs) anyone over him due to the balance of decision making on what is worth their time, while the small guilds that on any one day do NOT have the people to take him out, and have to plan for it so people go out of their way to log on are completely screwed because they never get him.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but that's really what it boils down to. The rotation itself is designed to keep harmony by giving *everyone* an equal shot at it, without brute force coming into effect. The big guilds take a hit in the number of times the kill the mob versus how many they could kill it, out of their desire to maintain order and hell, just to be fair in many guild leader's cases. Seeing medium level guilds that are shooting on up to higher content call for the end of rotations on mobs just because they only get X shots per unit time (the same amount of shots as every other guild on the rot) and feel the need for warriors to get hate giving weapons to MT in Velious/Luclin/PoP is understandable, but isn't fair.<br>
<br>
The rotation itself is an indication of desirability. Sure, sev is kunark content. Sure, most of the loot sucks compared to droppable crap out of later expansions, but he is still desired for those green scales. The fact 20+ guilds are on the rot show just how desired he is, and shows why a rot is needed. Ending the rot on sev would end up meaning 2-4 guilds would kill him every time. Race mob style.<br>
